messages.content:
Plan:
- Use Python to search YouTube for the BBC Earth video “Top 5 Silliest Animal Moments”.
- Open the first video result and extract its description.
- Scan the description for common bird names to identify the species featured.

Python script (run as is):
```python
# Python script to find the bird species featured in "Top 5 Silliest Animal Moments" BBC Earth video on YouTube
import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import urllib.parse
import re

headers = {
    "User-Agent": "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/112.0.0.0 Safari/537.36",
}

query = "Top 5 Silliest Animal Moments BBC Earth"
search_url = "https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=" + urllib.parse.quote(query)

sess = requests.Session()
resp = sess.get(search_url, headers=headers, timeout=15)
resp.raise_for_status()
soup = BeautifulSoup(resp.text, "html.parser")

video_href = None
for a in soup.find_all("a", href=True):
    href = a["href"]
    if href.startswith("/watch?v="):
        video_href = href
        break

if not video_href:
    raise SystemExit("Could not find a YouTube video link in search results.")

video_url = "https://www.youtube.com" + video_href
resp2 = sess.get(video_url, headers=headers, timeout=20)
resp2.raise_for_status()
soup2 = BeautifulSoup(resp2.text, "html.parser")

desc = None
# Try meta description
m = soup2.find("meta", attrs={"name": "description"})
if m and m.get("content"):
    desc = m["content"]
# Fallback to og:description
if not desc:
    m = soup2.find("meta", attrs={"property": "og:description"})
    if m and m.get("content"):
        desc = m["content"]

if not desc:
    # As a last resort, search in the page text
    text = soup2.get_text(" ", strip=True)
    match = re.search(r"description\s*:?[^.\n]+\.?", text, re.IGNORECASE)
    if match:
        desc = match.group(0)

if not desc:
    raise SystemExit("Could not extract video description from the YouTube page.")

desc_lc = (desc or "").lower()

bird_names = [
    "parrot","macaw","cockatoo","cockatiel","budgerigar","budgie","puffin","penguin",
    "owl","eagle","hawk","falcon","crow","raven","sparrow","finch","canary",
    "geese","goose","swan","pelican","flamingo","toucan","kingfisher","heron","crane",
    "parakeet","lovebird","nuthatch","grackle"
]

found = [name for name in bird_names if name in desc_lc]
print("Birds mentioned in video description:", found)

if not found:
    print("No bird species detected in the description.")
else:
    print("Detected bird species (possible):", ", ".join(found))
``` 

Run this script as-is. It will print any bird species mentioned in the video description. If you share the output, I’ll confirm the exact bird species featured.
